pageContext.description: Round shank flattened at head and turned round upon itself to hold ring which is grooved. Ring flat and the lower half filled in with a panel with scalloped edge. The face decorated on a rope pattern ground, with beaded sunk rounds - four of them perforated. 3 of them containing a boss. All connected up with faceted scallops. Also 2 triangular bosses. The ring is only corroded in one patch underneath, otherwise very even and clear cut.
pageContext.patina: Black patina with metal showing through. Patina on ring is even black
pageContext.surface: Surface on shank very slightly corroded.
pageContext.collection: Museum of Archaeology and Ethnology, Cambridge,No. 231 Murray Collection
